Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:02.50,Base,,0,0,0,,If men can protect… why does {\u1\1c&H0037AFD4&}God{\u0\1c&H00FFFFFF&} allow?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.50,0:00:06.00,Base,,0,0,0,,I’ve survived bullets.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.00,0:00:10.00,Base,,0,0,0,,I left my body and came back to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.00,0:00:14.00,Base,,0,0,0,,I’ve buried siblings, a father, and friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.00,0:00:18.00,Base,,0,0,0,,I know pain — and I know God’s faithfulness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.00,0:00:23.00,Base,,0,0,0,,But Charlie is gone at 31 — a father of two.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.00,0:00:27.00,Base,,0,0,0,,If men can shield, is God less resourceful?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.00,0:00:31.00,Base,,0,0,0,,I’m not doubting God. I’m wrestling with Him.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.00,0:00:35.00,Base,,0,0,0,,Truth matters because lies destroy. Fathers must engage.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.00,0:00:38.00,Base,,0,0,0,,Do you wrestle with God’s justice? Comment below.
